TiO2 NPs were prepared using a biphasic solvothermal (BST) reaction where the reaction takes place at the interface of water and organic solutions at an elevated temperature71,72. First, a water solution consisting of 20 ml of DI water and 200 µl of TEA (as a pH regulator) was added into a PTFE Teflon liner. Afterward, the organic solution was prepared by adding 800 µl of titanium (IV) isopropoxide and 1200 µl OA to 20 ml of heptane. The heptane solution was sonicated for 30 minutes in an ultrasonic bath (FS30H, Fisher Scientific) and then was poured gently over the water phase in the PTFE liner. The Teflon vessel was placed into a stainless steel autoclave, then sealed and heated in a vacuum oven (Thermo Scientific Heratherm™, USA) for 8 hours at 200 °C. Titanium (IV) isopropoxide reacted with water at the water/heptane interface to generate TiO2 as follows73:1Ti[OCH(CH3)2]4+2H2O→TiO2+4(CH3)2CHOH\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
